    <h1>Government Health Policies in India</h1>

    <h2>Introduction</h2>
    <p>Government health policies in India are instrumental in addressing the unique healthcare needs of its vast and diverse population. Their impact on public health cannot be overstated, as they strive to make quality healthcare accessible to all, control diseases, and improve healthcare infrastructure. These policies are not only crucial for improving health outcomes but also for achieving broader socio-economic development in the nation.</p>
    <br>
    <h2>Key Policies</h2>
    <p>Certainly, here are some key government health policies and initiatives in India:</p>

    <ol>
        <li>
            <strong>Ayushman Bharat - Pradhan Mantri Jan Arogya Yojana (PM-JAY):</strong>
            <ul>
                <li>Launched in 2018, Ayushman Bharat is one of the largest healthcare insurance schemes globally.</li>
                <li>It provides health insurance coverage to over 100 million vulnerable families, offering financial protection for hospitalization expenses.</li>
                <li><a href="https://ab-hwc.nhp.gov.in/">Click here to know more about the program.</a></li>
            </ul>
            <h3>Here are the common document requirements:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Proof of Identity (PoI)</li>
                <li>Proof of Residence (PoR)</li>
                <li>Proof of Family Size</li>
                <li>Income Certificate</li>
                <li>Caste Certificate</li>
                <li>Hospitalization Documents</li>
                <li>Family Declaration Form</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong>National Health Mission (NHM):</strong>
            <ul>
                <li>The NHM is a flagship program that aims to provide accessible, affordable, and quality healthcare to rural and urban areas.</li>
                <li>It encompasses various sub-programs, including the National Rural Health Mission (NRHM) and the National Urban Health Mission (NUHM).</li>
                <li><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/National_Health_Mission">Click here to know more about the program.</a></li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong>Janani Suraksha Yojana (JSY):</strong>
            <ul>
                <li>JSY is a safe motherhood intervention under the NHM, which promotes institutional deliveries by providing cash incentives to pregnant women who deliver in healthcare facilities.</li>
                <li><a href="https://www.myscheme.gov.in/schemes/jsy">Click here to know more about the program.</a></li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong>National Rural Health Mission (NRHM):</strong>
            <ul>
                <li>Focused on improving healthcare infrastructure in rural areas, NRHM aims to strengthen primary healthcare centers, provide essential drugs and equipment, and train healthcare workers.</li>
                <li><a href="https://www.vikaspedia.in/health/nrhm/national-health-mission/national-rural-health-mission-nrhm">Click here to know more about the program.</a></li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong>National Urban Health Mission (NUHM):</strong>
            <ul>
                <li>This program concentrates on addressing the healthcare needs of urban populations through the establishment of urban health centers and promoting urban health.</li>
                <li><a href="https://nhsrcindia.org/practice-areas/kmd/urban-health-nuhm">Click here to know more about the program.</a></li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong>Pulse Polio Program:</strong>
            <ul>
                <li>The Pulse Polio program aims to eradicate polio by conducting regular vaccination campaigns across the country.</li>
                <li><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pulse_Polio">Click here to know more about the program.</a></li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong>Revised National Tuberculosis Control Program (RNTCP):</strong>
            <ul>
                <li>RNTCP focuses on the diagnosis and treatment of tuberculosis (TB) in India. It aims to provide universal access to TB care.</li>
                <li><a href="https://main.mohfw.gov.in/?q=Organisation/Departments%20of%20Health%20and%20Family%20Welfare/revised-national-tuberculosis-programme">Click here to know more about the program.</a></li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong>National Vector Borne Disease Control Program (NVBDCP):</strong>
            <ul>
                <li>NVBDCP addresses vector-borne diseases like malaria, dengue, and lymphatic filariasis by implementing preventive measures and providing treatment.</li>
                <li><a href="https://ncvbdc.mohfw.gov.in/">Click here to know more about the program.</a></li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong>National AIDS Control Program (NACP):</strong>
            <ul>
                <li>NACP is responsible for HIV/AIDS prevention, control, and management. It includes targeted interventions, awareness campaigns, and treatment services.</li>
                <li><a href="https://cleartax.in/s/nacp-national-aids-control-programme">Click here to know more about the program.</a></li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong>Mental Healthcare Act, 2017:</strong>
            <ul>
                <li>This act aims to provide mental healthcare and services to individuals with mental illnesses and protect their rights.</li>
                <li><a href="https://www.indiacode.nic.in/handle/123456789/2249">Click here to know more about the program.</a></li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong>Swachh Bharat Abhiyan (Clean India Campaign):</strong>
            <ul>
                <li>While not solely a healthcare policy, Swachh Bharat aims to improve sanitation and hygiene, which has a significant impact on public health by reducing the spread of waterborne diseases.</li>
                <li><a href="https://www.pmindia.gov.in/en/major_initiatives/swachh-bharat-abhiyan/">Click here to know more about the program.</a></li>
            </ul>
        </li>
    </ol>
